6. Who Didn't Make The Cut?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(6.1) Python

You could possibly consider the pythons to be the Python language, but there's really no canonical Python character that's associated with Python except the python branding. Indeed, the Python name doesn't even refer to the snake, but rather to Monty Python, the British comedy troupe. So while snakes are often used in Python branding and logos, there isn't a specific mascot character that represents the language in the same way as other languages.







