[^1]: Why doesn't Windows have a mascot, you might be wondering? Well, there *are* several unofficial Windows mascots created by fans called OS-tans, anime anthropomorphizations of the various Windows operating systems that have been popular in fringe internet culture. It started when users of Windows ME started drawing anthropomorphized characters to represent the operating system, often portraying it as a girl with a somewhat unstable personality, which is supposed to reflect the reputation Windows ME had for being buggy and unreliable. I had started looking into this but it gets very weird very fast, so I'll leave it as an exercise for the reader to delve into that rabbit hole.

